# Commit Storytelling

- Commit continuously in small, logical increments.
- Make each commit easy to review in isolation.
- Write commit messages that explain intent and rationale, not just the diff.
- Never use placeholder commit messages like "WIP".
- Structure the full commit sequence so it tells a coherent, end-to-end story.
